ith China's Zhang Boheng for the all around title, Hashimoto's medal hopes were dashed when he slipped off the pommel horse after losing his balance going into a handstand.\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 963, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 795, \"end\": 800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.5589079132044185, \"rank\": 0.7862824113342896, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 803, \"end\": 815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Boheng\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zhang Boheng\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Boheng\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zhang_Boheng\"}, {\"begin\": 842, \"end\": 851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daiki_Hashimoto\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.100341429033231e-24, \"text\": \"Hashimoto\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daiki_Hashimoto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daiki_Hashimoto\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the all around title\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 840}, {\"ngram\": \"the pommel horse\", \"from\": 898, \"to\": 914}, {\"ngram\": \"his balance\", \"from\": 928, \"to\": 939}, {\"ngram\": \"a handstand\", \"from\": 951, \"to\": 962}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It proved to be a costly error that ultimately placed him sixth.\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 1028, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a costly error\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 994}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is a chance to try again,\\\" the 22-year-old told reporters through tears after the event, in which compatriot Shinnosuke Oka took the gold and Zhang the silver.\", \"from\": 1030, \"to\": 1196, 